text:
Hi I'm                                                        Kamalei 
                                                        I want to become a genuine indie hacker, building products and
                                                        services that hold value for both myself and others. I will
                                                        share my ideas, successes, and failures here.

Redesigned                                                        how Chronote’s timeline is rendered. It now determines the
                                                        merging intervals for app activities according to the magnitude
                                                        of the time range, aligning with natural human intuition—larger
                                                        ranges require a higher level of abstraction.

This                                                        design inspiration does not come from AI. Although AI is very
                                                        powerful, it cannot judge what is truly good. Therefore, I want
                                                        to emphasize that those engaged in vibe coding will always be
                                                        the helmsmen.

Major                                                        architecture shift for Chronote: embedding a Kernel MCP server.

                                                        Moving beyond just "visualizing data" to becoming the "temporal
                                                        memory" for AI. Launching both GUI and CLI in GA. AI can finally
                                                        understand how your time is actually spent.                                                       #BuildInPublic                                                      #macOS

The                                                        hardest part of being an independent software developer is not
                                                        building the software, but rather the product itself and its
                                                        promotion. The most challenging aspect of the product lies in
                                                        discovering and verifying user needs.

Investigations                                                        and research on demands can be done quickly using some tools and
                                                        scientific methods, such as using Google Trends to explore
                                                        demands.For verified requirements, we should quickly iterate to
                                                        a sufficiently good state.

If                                                        there are still no users, should we suspect it's a product issue
                                                        or a promotion reason?

The                                                        essence of my using a time tracking tool is to have it help me
                                                        explain what I did in a day and what I did in a week.
                                                      #chronote

I think                                                        we shouldn't rely entirely on AI for explanations. Instead, I
                                                        believe that more can be done to make answers automatically
                                                        presented through appropriate charts and UI, without the need
                                                        for excessive explanations.
